# HTTP API base URL for the AI consult endpoint (POST /api/consult -- see
# docs/feature-spec.md F4 v0.2 and lambdas/llm/handler.py). This is the API Gateway
# base URL, e.g. `terraform output api_predict_url` with the trailing /api/predict
# stripped -- it is NOT the CloudFront domain (fleet_data.json is same-origin via
# CloudFront; /api/* is a separate origin and is not proxied through it).
#
# Copy this file to .env (gitignored) for local dev, or set VITE_API_BASE as a repo
# variable in CI (see .github/workflows/frontend-deploy.yml). Left unset, api.js's
# consultAI() no-ops and App.jsx falls back to the local aiAnswer() stub.
VITE_API_BASE=https://xxxxxxxxxx.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com
